# Environment Variables for Production (Vercel)

When deploying to Vercel, you will need to add these variables in the "Settings" > "Environment Variables" section.

## Database (Vercel Postgres)
If you add a Vercel Postgres database during deployment, these will be added automatically.
- `POSTGRES_URL`
- `POSTGRES_PRISMA_URL`
- `POSTGRES_URL_NON_POOLING`

## Authentication (NextAuth.js)
- `NEXTAUTH_URL`: Your Vercel domain (e.g., https://shuniqit-store.vercel.app)
- `NEXTAUTH_SECRET`: A random string (you can generate one by typing `openssl rand -base64 32` in terminal or just smashing your keyboard randomly for now like `Jd83kd92...`)

## Payments (Stripe & PayPal)
- `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY`: Your Stripe Live Secret Key
- `STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY`: Your Stripe Live Publishable Key
- `PAYPAL_CLIENT_ID`: Your PayPal Live Client ID
